data.value:
Composing forms
Click on the blue plus () button in the designer window to add new form fields. Move individual fields by dragging the handle () or header displayed when hovering over a field. Existing fields can be removed by clicking the delete () icon.

Use the gray buttons on the left and right edges of the designer window to add or adjust sections, which define the form's overall layout.

data.name: kentico.formbuilder.component.recaptcha.description
data.value: Provides a robust CAPTCHA service based on reCAPTCHA, which requires the user to click a checkbox indicating the user is not a robot. This will either pass the user immediately (with No CAPTCHA) or challenge them to validate whether or not they are human.

data.name: kentico.formbuilder.smartfield.tooltip
data.value: Smart fields allow you to collect data over multiple form submissions, which helps keep your forms short and easy to complete. They are not displayed in the form initially, but instead progressively replace fields for which the user has already submitted a value. The total number of displayed fields is determined by the number of non-smart fields in the form. Important: Smart fields only appear for visitors who are tracked as contacts and view the form again after a previous submission.

data.value: To specify the list of options: a) Type one value per line. In this case, the value saved into the field is the same as the option's displayed text. For example: Option1 Option2 b) Type value and text pairs in format value;text (each on a new line). The value is saved into the field and the text is displayed in the list of options. For example: usa;United States cz;Czech Republic
